In my opinion, this should not be true at all, both because I don't think massive snowballs are fun to watch, and also because** in the LCS or other competitive play they were ALREADY able to exploit their advantages to snowball**. Both this summer and last Worlds had many games closed at min 30 (short) because when a team were winning, they managed to press their advantage. In fact, I think that they're gonna have to fix the current snowbally state of things for competitive play, cause if not it's reaaaaally gonna be boring.

Just what I think. Love the image btw, didn't know you could put this ;)
